ugging for endless errors =&gt; passing test cases and chosen edge cases, and submitting<br /><br />posting pseudo code might help people skip some important steps in understanding and doing the assignment themselves, by giving them an idea of what logistical structures might work to solve the problem stated in the lab instructions, and how to implement them. this is just my opinion though - I don&#39;t think pseudo code should be allowed on piazza."}], "type": "s_answer", "tag_endorse_arr": ["jlzv60dhucu1fm", "lm7ukt2fxpd31m"], "children": [], "id": "lss0mjd0rdz5fg", "config": {"editor": "rte"}, "is_tag_endorse": false}, {"history_size": 1, "folders": [], "data": {"embed_links": []}, "created": "2024-02-19T22:26:02Z", "bucket_order": 3, "tag_endorse": [{"role": "student", "name": "Aadavan Vasudevan", "endorser": {}, "admin": false, "photo": null, "id": "lm7ukt2fxpd31m", "photo_url": null, "published": true, "us": false, "facebook_id": null}], "bucket_name": "Today", "history": [{"anon": "no", "uid": "jlzv60dhucu1fm", "subject": "", "created": "2024-02-19T22:26:02Z", "content": "<p>I wholeheartedly agree with the student&#39;s response! </p>
<p></p>
<p>Sharing pseudo code does indeed solve part of the assignment and allows students to skip steps in the process of writing code. In fact, in previous years, many students shared pseudo code with one another resulting in 90%&#43; similar code. Cases like that constitutes as an academic integrity violation. </p>
<p></p>
<p>You can help each other if a classmate asks about &#34;I don&#39;t understand how do we write a loop,&#34; &#34;I think I don&#39;t know how do I think about the condition of a loop,&#34; &#34;I don&#39;t think I understand what part 2 in lab 5 is asking us to do,&#34; &#34;I am getting this error and I don&#39;t know where does it come from.&#34; These are all general questions, and don&#39;t relate to the lab, and wouldn&#39;t result in having the same code. </p>
<p></p>
<p>On a side note, as an educator, I feel happy to read the students steps to create their programs. This is exactly what we teach you to do, and seeing that you do so makes me feel proud! </p>"}], "type": "i_answer", "tag_endorse_arr": ["lm7ukt2fxpd31m"], "children": [], "id": "lsti9tsoody3a7", "config": {"editor": "rte"}, "is_tag_endorse": false}], "tag_good_arr": ["lm6unadbfxc6rw", "lm7ukr1754d2wl"], "no_answer": 0, "id": "lspbvf5v4xy5qk", "config": {"editor": "rte", "has_emails_sent": 1}, "status": "active", "drafts": {}, "request_instructor": 0, "request_instructor_me": false, "bookmarked": 2, "num_favorites": 0, "my_favorite": false, "is_bookmarked": false, "is_tag_good": false, "q_edits": [], "i_edits": [], "s_edits": [], "t": 1716162801696, "default_anonymity": "no"}

{"history_size": 1, "folders": ["midterm"], "nr": 572, "data": {"embed_links": []}, "created": "2024-02-24T03:55:35Z", "bucket_order": 3, "no_answer_followup": 0, "change_log": [{"anon": "stud", "data": "lszjt1rxumq36m", "v": "all", "type": "create", "when": "2024-02-24T03:55:35Z", "uid_a": "a_0"}, {"anon": "no", "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "data": "lszjttyi9uu9a", "to": "lszjt1roq6o36k", "type": "s_answer", "when": "2024-02-24T03:56:12Z"}, {"anon": "no", "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "data": "lszju5b8t9vqp", "type": "s_answer_update", "when": "2024-02-24T03:56:26Z"}, {"anon": "no", "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "data": "lszjvt0yxkr3ed", "type": "s_answer_update", "when": "2024-02-24T03:57:44Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "to": "lszjt1roq6o36k", "type": "followup", "when": "2024-02-24T03:58:15Z", "cid": "lszjwhe8fod1ju", "uid_a": "a_0"}, {"anon": "no", "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "to": "lszjt1roq6o36k", "type": "feedback", "when": "2024-02-24T04:05:45Z", "cid": "lszk64ocbns4wr"}, {"anon": "stud", "to": "lszjt1roq6o36k", "type": "feedback", "when": "2024-02-24T04:11:30Z", "cid": "lszkdiebxpj7dm", "uid_a": "a_0"}, {"anon": "no", "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "to": "lszjt1roq6o36k", "type": "feedback", "when": "2024-02-24T04:14:00Z", "cid": "lszkgq2yfmb6l7"}], "bucket_name": "Today", "history": [{"anon": "stud", "uid_a": "a_0", "subject": "2019 Midterm Question 9 Inquiry", "created": "2024-02-24T03:55:35Z", "content": "<p>How come we don&#39;t need a return line at the end of each function?</p>
<p></p>
<p><img src="/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Flm7ul3hccbr41t%2F71a04063a9f6c94d7c3dcafb7e2abdee3e1147c0212a5be088b535c5dc03892d%2Fimage.png" alt="image.pngNaN" /></p>"}], "type": "question", "tags": ["midterm", "student"], "tag_good": [], "unique_views": 40, "children": [{"history_size": 3, "folders": [], "data": {"embed_links": []}, "created": "2024-02-24T03:56:12Z", "bucket_order": 3, "tag_endorse": [{"role": "instructor", "name": "Salma Emara", "endorser": {}, "admin": true, "photo": "1675320204_200.jpg", "id": "jlzv60dhucu1fm", "photo_url": "https://cdn-uploads.piazza.com/photos/jlzv60dhucu1fm/1675320204_200.jpg", "published": true, "us": false, "facebook_id": null}], "bucket_name": "Today", "history": [{"anon": "no", "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "subject": "", "created": "2024-02-24T03:57:44Z", "content": "The return type is <kbd>void</kbd>, which means that nothing is expected to be returned, so you don&#39;t need a <kbd>return</kbd> statement."}, {"anon": "no", "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "subject": "", "created": "2024-02-24T03:56:26Z", "content": "The return type is <kbd>void</kbd>, so nothing is expected to be returned."}, {"anon": "no", "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "subject": "", "created": "2024-02-24T03:56:12Z", "content": "The return type is void, so nothing is expected to be returned."}], "type": "s_answer", "tag_endorse_arr": ["jlzv60dhucu1fm"], "children": [], "id": "lszjttycgcy99", "config": {"editor": "rte"}, "is_tag_endorse": false}, {"anon": "stud", "folders": [], "data": {"embed_links": null}, "no_upvotes": 0, "subject": "What does it mean for a return type to be void? How does the main function continue if the other functions don&#39;t return anything?", "created": "2024-02-24T03:58:15Z", "bucket_order": 6, "bucket_name": "Last week", "type": "followup", "tag_good": [], "uid_a": "a_0", "children": [{"anon": "no", "folders": [], "data": {"embed_links": null}, "subject": "<p>It just means that the function does not return any values. When the function is called, it will run all statements in that function and then go back to executing statements where it was originally called.</p>
<p></p>
<p>For example, consider:</p>
<p></p>
<pre>
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

void printHello(void) {
	printf(&#34;Hello (in printHello())!\n&#34;);
}

int main(void) {
	printHello();
	printf(&#34;Hello (in main())!\n&#34;);
	return 0;
}</pre>
<p></p>
<p>The output of this program would be:</p>
<p></p>
<p><kbd>Hello (in printHello())!</kbd></p>
<p><kbd>Hello (in main())!</kbd></p>
<p></p>
<p>This is because it first calls <kbd>printHello()</kbd>, so it runs all the statements in that function, and then once it finishes, it runs the subsequent statements in <kbd>main()</kbd>.</p>
<p></p>", "created": "2024-02-24T04:05:45Z", "bucket_order": 6, "bucket_name": "Last week", "type": "feedback", "tag_good": [{"role": "student", "name": "Hanna Bui", "endorser": {}, "admin": false, "photo": null, "id": "lm7ul3hccbr41t", "photo_url": null, "us": false, "facebook_id": null}], "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "children": [], "tag_good_arr": ["lm7ul3hccbr41t"], "id": "lszk64ocbns4wr", "updated": "2024-02-24T04:11:38Z", "config": {"editor": "rte"}}, {"anon": "stud", "folders": [], "data": {"embed_links": null}, "subject": "<p>I see, but then in this question, how do the integers feet and inches in the main function get the values of *outFeet and *outInches from the getInput function?</p>
<p></p>
<p><img src="/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Flm7ul3hccbr41t%2F4e1eb7a858bd8a2c93ad3c401b4fcd7c545c4757311edc366602843a0b823b87%2Fimage.png" alt="image.pngNaN" /></p>", "created": "2024-02-24T04:11:30Z", "bucket_order": 6, "bucket_name": "Last week", "type": "feedback", "tag_good": [], "uid_a": "a_0", "children": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "id": "lszkdiebxpj7dm", "updated": "2024-02-24T04:11:30Z", "config": {"editor": "rte"}}, {"anon": "no", "folders": [], "data": {"embed_links": null}, "subject": "That&#39;s because the solution is using pointers to directly change the values of <kbd>feet</kbd> and <kbd>inches</kbd> (notice how the parameters for <kbd>getInput()</kbd> are integer pointers).", "created": "2024-02-24T04:14:00Z", "bucket_order": 6, "bucket_name": "Last week", "type": "feedback", "tag_good": [{"role": "student", "name": "Hanna Bui", "endorser": {}, "admin": false, "photo": null, "id": "lm7ul3hccbr41t", "photo_url": null, "us": false, "facebook_id": null}], "uid": "lm0w6sz9wqg54e", "children": [], "tag_good_arr": ["lm7ul3hccbr41t"], "id": "lszkgq2yfmb6l7", "updated": "2024-02-24T04:15:44Z", "config": {"editor": "rte"}}], "tag_good_arr": [], "no_answer": 0, "id": "lszjwhe8fod1ju", "updated": "2024-02-24T04:16:18Z", "config": {"editor": "rte"}}], "tag_good_arr": [], "no_answer": 0, "id": "lszjt1roq6o36k", "config": {"editor": "rte", "has_emails_sent": 1}, "status": "active", "drafts": {}, "request_instructor": 0, "request_instructor_me": false, "bookmarked": 1, "num_favorites": 0, "my_favorite": false, "is_bookmarked": false, "is_tag_good": false, "q_edits": [], "i_edits": [], "s_edits": [], "t": 1716162897545, "default_anonymity": "no"}

